        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 52. Gymnopus pinophilus. Cheilocystidia. A Cluster of two cheilocystidia B-H Individual cheilocystidia. Standard bars = 10 µm. TFB 7234 (TENN-F- 53553)." , "Figure 51. Gymnopus pinophilus. Basidiospores. Standard bars = 5 µm. A = TFB 14097. B = TFB 10459 (TENN-F- 67804)." , "Figure 49. Gymnopus pinophilus. Broom cell-like hyphal termini of pileipellis. A Diverticula in slime matrix B, C Individual elements D Gelatinizing broom cell-like termini. Standard bars = 10 µm. DED 4491 (TENN-F- 54655)." , "Figure 48. Gymnopus pinophilus. Pileipellis elements. A Encrusted hyphae showing crust material in slime sheath B Hyphae with gelatinized walls C Diverticulate hypha showing dichotomous diverticula. Standard bars = 10 µm. DED 4491 (TENN-F- 54665)." , "Figure 47. Gymnopus pinophilus. Basidiomata on needles of Pinus strobus. Standard bars = 20 mm. Above: TFB 14511. Below: TFB 14059 (TENN-F- 67804)." , "Figure 50. Gymnopus pinophilus. Hymenial elements. A-D Pleurocystidia E-H Basidia. Standard bars = 10 µm. DED 4491 (TENN-F- 54665)." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/115112" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/115110" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/115109" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/115113" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/115114" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/115111" .

